process by which inland law becomes maritime law -- is our
process, maintained by our Assessors, sworn at our Shrine.

The Mirror Flats are our outer boundary. From the signal towers,
the Flats' salt crust reveals approaching caravans for miles.
We see them before they see us. By design.

The Glasswind Belts are our natural defense and our deepest scar.
The thermal pulse that destroyed the Scorched Wastes fused our sand
into brittle glass. We built on that glass. Every guardian-name
sworn at the Shrine acknowledges this: we are the city the
disaster made.

The Tariff Cairn Lines fed directly into our Ledger Houses. Three
parallel routes -- Swift Line, Heavy Road, Sealed Route -- each
required different attestation. Our four Ledger Houses descend from
those cairn assessors. The Quarantine Ledger descends from the
Sealed Route's relic handlers, who classified pyramid-origin
artifacts before Mafdet had walls.

The Shoreward Seal at the Tidemouth Dunes is where the Dual-
Attestation Protocol takes physical form. Inland provenance verified
against charter stamps. Maritime risk assessed against vessel and
season. Both must align before the harbor chain drops. No
exceptions. No appeals to urgency. No waivers for rank.

The Reach Wardens patrolling the cairn lines are our first
intelligence. When their reports indicate disrupted caravans or
unattested cargo in the Glasswind Belts, the Harbor Wardens raise
the chain and the Ledger Houses increase inspection thresholds.

The Glasswalk Guides are strictly neutral. They guide anyone who
pays. That is honest commerce. But we note who they guide, when,
and from which direction.

The Red Sand Outriders from our debt-leverage consortium prey on
distressed caravans -- but bring goods otherwise lost. The Ledger
Houses process their cargo under amber-seal protocols. Mafdet pays
fairly, and fairly includes uncomfortable means of arrival.
Salt remembers the river. Glass remembers the
catastrophe. Cairns remember the old law. The Shoreward Conversion
remembers all of it, translating broken history into clean manifests
and sworn oaths. That is what we are.

